  <stage stageid="a8d23a61-e2be-4aa0-9e2a-393c0c8f063a" name="new" type="Note">
    <subsheetid>704d2411-3199-4ae6-8c78-38529781a406</subsheetid>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <display x="-180" y="60" w="180" h="230"/>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="315981c4-3bac-4773-af8f-7e3f2d2db4e1" name="new" type="Note">
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
    <display x="-180" y="60" w="180" h="230"/>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>

  <stage stageid="7a8bec24-76d2-4591-a717-40b231a2d58f" name="new" type="Note">
    <subsheetid>85b21362-8ee0-4c3b-8532-1c194626a6e8</subsheetid>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="52652c24-9ddc-42ed-9d12-7987b8c6583c" name="new" type="Note">
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>

    <stage stageid="91c46163-e545-48a9-88a1-0a58671b098e" name="new" type="Note">
      <subsheetid>41dfd7c5-86c2-4692-bbb9-94c4b7533543</subsheetid>
      <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
      <displayx>-180</displayx>
      <displayy>60</displayy>
      <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
      <displayheight>230</displayheight>
      <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
    </stage>
    <stage stageid="7b462e83-d587-4e82-9065-920b68d819e8" name="new" type="Note">
      <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
      <displayx>-180</displayx>
      <displayy>60</displayy>
      <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
      <displayheight>230</displayheight>
      <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
    </stage>

  <stage stageid="e5502a51-4604-4d8b-82c2-ca76d9c79b0a" name="new" type="Note">
    <subsheetid>4bff7d25-9ea5-4022-b112-e8656cd98f28</subsheetid>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="78b57eb2-dd62-4e6b-bec7-b60610e6f09f" name="new" type="Note">
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>

    <subsheetid>37e947ce-3f76-4266-8a78-7c31d24564eb</subsheetid>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="1e153f85-dbad-4efe-bbdf-2360d4c34371" name="new" type="Note">
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>

    <subsheetid>cfb6da91-518b-40a3-8e0e-115ff0252ea7</subsheetid>
    <loginhibit/>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="7bb7dcd7-acf2-4a7a-a96d-756830b2e54f" name="new" type="Note">
    <loginhibit/>
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>

	oCommand = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand

	If Not moTransaction Is Nothing Then

    <code>
Dim oCommand As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand

Success = False
Message = ""

Try
	oCommand = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
	oCommand.Connection = moConnection
	oCommand.CommandType = System.Data.CommandType.Text
	oCommand.CommandText = SQL

    <code>
Dim oCommand As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
Dim oDataAdapter As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlDataAdapter
Dim oDataSet As System.Data.DataSet

Success = False
Message = ""

Try
	oCommand = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
	oCommand.Connection = moConnection
	oCommand.CommandType = System.Data.CommandType.Text
	oCommand.CommandText = SQL

	oDataAdapter = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlDataAdapter
	oDataAdapter .SelectCommand = oCommand
	oDataset = New System.Data.DataSet		
	oDataAdapter.Fill(oDataset)
	Results = oDataSet.Tables(0)
	Success = True

Catch ex As System.Exception
	Message = ex.Message
End Try</code>

  <stage stageid="8320d0fa-e927-4629-8954-b96fab0f46fc" name="new" type="Note">
    <subsheetid>99085ae8-52aa-4274-ab3b-803483c84f53</subsheetid>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <display x="-180" y="60" w="180" h="230"/>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="74ee633a-8129-46cd-a340-c12024f4a694" name="new" type="Note">
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
    <display x="-180" y="60" w="180" h="230"/>

  <stage stageid="6f981412-9a8b-4c94-b883-7adcdd81c53f" name="new" type="Note">
    <subsheetid>5f45c088-6c82-4037-bb47-2dc25151bb0a</subsheetid>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="1c65dd31-6f31-4e61-b1c9-146f63528a42" name="new" type="Note">
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
    <displayx>-180</displayx>
    <displayy>60</displayy>
    <displaywidth>180</displaywidth>
    <displayheight>230</displayheight>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>

  <stage stageid="6f981412-9a8b-4c94-b883-7adcdd81c53f" name="new" type="Note">
    <subsheetid>5f45c088-6c82-4037-bb47-2dc25151bb0a</subsheetid>
    <narrative>Clean Up Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.

The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.</narrative>
    <display x="-180" y="60" w="180" h="230"/>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
  <stage stageid="1c65dd31-6f31-4e61-b1c9-146f63528a42" name="new" type="Note">
    <narrative>Initialise Page

This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.

The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.

You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.</narrative>
    <display x="-180" y="60" w="180" h="230"/>
    <font family="Tahoma" size="10" style="Regular" color="000000"/>
  </stage>
